{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I learned about the Haiti earthquake by Skype."},{"time":4000,"text":"My wife sent me a message,"},{"time":7000,"text":"\"Whoa, earthquake,\""},{"time":9000,"text":"and then disappeared for 25 minutes."},{"time":13000,"text":"It was 25 minutes of absolute terror"},{"time":16000,"text":"that thousands of people across the U.S. felt."},{"time":21000,"text":"I was afraid of a tsunami;"},{"time":24000,"text":"what I didn't realize"},{"time":26000,"text":"was there was a greater terror in Haiti,"},{"time":29000,"text":"and that was building collapse."},{"time":32000,"text":"We've all seen the photos"},{"time":34000,"text":"of the collapsed buildings in Haiti."},{"time":37000,"text":"These are shots my wife took"},{"time":39000,"text":"a couple days after the quake,"},{"time":41000,"text":"while I was making my way through the D.R. into the country."},{"time":45000,"text":"This is the national palace --"},{"time":47000,"text":"the equivalent of the White House."},{"time":50000,"text":"This is the largest supermarket in the Caribbean"},{"time":53000,"text":"at peak shopping time."},{"time":58000,"text":"This is a nurses' college --"},{"time":60000,"text":"there are 300 nurses studying."},{"time":64000,"text":"The general hospital right next door"},{"time":66000,"text":"emerged largely unscathed."},{"time":69000,"text":"This is the Ministry of Economics and Finance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75000,"text":"We have all heard"},{"time":77000,"text":"about the tremendous human loss"},{"time":80000,"text":"in the earthquake in Haiti,"},{"time":82000,"text":"but we haven't heard enough"},{"time":85000,"text":"about why all those lives were lost."},{"time":88000,"text":"We haven't heard about"},{"time":90000,"text":"why the buildings failed."},{"time":93000,"text":"After all, it was the buildings,"},{"time":95000,"text":"not the earthquake,"},{"time":97000,"text":"that killed 220,000 people,"},{"time":100000,"text":"that injured 330,000,"},{"time":103000,"text":"that displaced 1.3 million people,"},{"time":109000,"text":"that cut off food"},{"time":111000,"text":"and water and supplies"},{"time":113000,"text":"for an entire nation."},{"time":116000,"text":"This is the largest metropolitan-area disaster"},{"time":121000,"text":"in decades,"},{"time":124000,"text":"and it was not a natural disaster --"},{"time":127000,"text":"it was a disaster of engineering."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130000,"text":"AIDG has worked in Haiti"},{"time":132000,"text":"since 2007,"},{"time":134000,"text":"providing engineering and business support"},{"time":136000,"text":"to small businesses."},{"time":138000,"text":"And after the quake, we started bringing in earthquake engineers"},{"time":142000,"text":"to figure out why the buildings collapsed,"},{"time":144000,"text":"to examine what was safe and what wasn't."},{"time":147000,"text":"Working with MINUSTAH,"},{"time":150000,"text":"which is the U.N. mission in Haiti,"},{"time":152000,"text":"with the Ministry of Public Works,"},{"time":154000,"text":"with different NGOs,"},{"time":156000,"text":"we inspected over 1,500 buildings."},{"time":160000,"text":"We inspected schools"},{"time":162000,"text":"and private residencies."},{"time":164000,"text":"We inspected medical centers"},{"time":166000,"text":"and food warehouses."},{"time":168000,"text":"We inspected government buildings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"This is the Ministry of Justice."},{"time":172000,"text":"Behind that door"},{"time":174000,"text":"is the National Judicial Archives."},{"time":177000,"text":"The fellow in the door, Andre Filitrault --"},{"time":179000,"text":"who's the director"},{"time":181000,"text":"of the Center for Interdisciplinary Earthquake Engineering Research"},{"time":185000,"text":"at the University of Buffalo --"},{"time":188000,"text":"was examining it to see if it was safe"},{"time":190000,"text":"to recover the archives."},{"time":192000,"text":"Andre told me,"},{"time":194000,"text":"after seeing these buildings fail"},{"time":196000,"text":"again and again in the same way,"},{"time":199000,"text":"that there is no new research here."},{"time":202000,"text":"There is nothing here that we don't know."},{"time":205000,"text":"The failure points were the same:"},{"time":208000,"text":"walls and slabs not tied properly into columns --"},{"time":211000,"text":"that's a roof slab hanging off the building --"},{"time":216000,"text":"cantilevered structures,"},{"time":218000,"text":"or structures that were asymmetric,"},{"time":220000,"text":"that shook violently and came down,"},{"time":224000,"text":"poor building materials,"},{"time":226000,"text":"not enough concrete,"},{"time":228000,"text":"not enough compression in the blocks,"},{"time":232000,"text":"rebar that was smooth,"},{"time":234000,"text":"rebar that was exposed to the weather and had rusted away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237000,"text":"Now there's a solution"},{"time":240000,"text":"to all these problems."},{"time":242000,"text":"And we know how to build properly."},{"time":245000,"text":"The proof of this came in Chile,"},{"time":248000,"text":"almost a month later,"},{"time":251000,"text":"when 8.8 magnitude earthquake"},{"time":255000,"text":"hit Chile."},{"time":257000,"text":"That is 500 times"},{"time":259000,"text":"the power of the 7.0"},{"time":261000,"text":"that hit Port-au-Prince --"},{"time":264000,"text":"500 times the power,"},{"time":266000,"text":"yet only under a thousand casualties."},{"time":271000,"text":"Adjusted for population density,"},{"time":273000,"text":"that is less than one percent"},{"time":275000,"text":"of the impact of the Haitian quake."},{"time":279000,"text":"What was the difference"},{"time":281000,"text":"between Chile and Haiti?"},{"time":284000,"text":"Seismic standards"},{"time":286000,"text":"and confined masonry,"},{"time":289000,"text":"where the building acts as a whole --"},{"time":291000,"text":"walls and columns"},{"time":293000,"text":"and roofs and slabs"},{"time":295000,"text":"tied together to support each other --"},{"time":298000,"text":"instead of breaking off into separate members and failing."},{"time":303000,"text":"If you look at this building in Chile,"},{"time":306000,"text":"it's ripped in half,"},{"time":308000,"text":"but it's not a pile of rubble."},{"time":312000,"text":"Chileans have been building with confined masonry"},{"time":314000,"text":"for decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"Right now, AIDG is working with KPFF Consulting Engineers,"},{"time":321000,"text":"Architecture for Humanity,"},{"time":323000,"text":"to bring more confined masonry training"},{"time":326000,"text":"into Haiti."},{"time":330000,"text":"This is Xantus Daniel;"},{"time":332000,"text":"he's a mason,"},{"time":334000,"text":"just a general construction worker, not a foreman,"},{"time":337000,"text":"who took one of our trainings."},{"time":339000,"text":"On his last job he was working with his boss,"},{"time":342000,"text":"and they started pouring the columns wrong."},{"time":345000,"text":"He took his boss aside,"},{"time":347000,"text":"and he showed him the materials on confined masonry."},{"time":350000,"text":"He showed him, \"You know, we don't have to do this wrong."},{"time":353000,"text":"It won't cost us any more"},{"time":355000,"text":"to do it the right way.\""},{"time":358000,"text":"And they redid that building."},{"time":360000,"text":"They tied the rebar right,"},{"time":362000,"text":"they poured the columns right,"},{"time":364000,"text":"and that building will be safe."},{"time":366000,"text":"And every building"},{"time":368000,"text":"that they build going forward"},{"time":370000,"text":"will be safe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"To make sure these buildings are safe,"},{"time":375000,"text":"it's not going to take policy --"},{"time":378000,"text":"it's going to take reaching out"},{"time":380000,"text":"to the masons on the ground"},{"time":383000,"text":"and helping them learn the proper techniques."},{"time":388000,"text":"Now there are many groups doing this."},{"time":390000,"text":"And the fellow in the vest there,"},{"time":392000,"text":"Craig Toten,"},{"time":394000,"text":"he has pushed forward"},{"time":396000,"text":"to get documentation out to all the groups that are doing this."},{"time":400000,"text":"Through Haiti Rewired,"},{"time":402000,"text":"through Build Change, Architecture for Humanity,"},{"time":405000,"text":"AIDG,"},{"time":407000,"text":"there is the possibility"},{"time":409000,"text":"to reach out"},{"time":412000,"text":"to 30,000 -- 40,000 masons"},{"time":415000,"text":"across the country"},{"time":417000,"text":"and create a movement of proper building."},{"time":422000,"text":"If you reach out to the people on the ground"},{"time":424000,"text":"in this collaborative way"},{"time":426000,"text":"it's extremely affordable."},{"time":429000,"text":"For the billions spent on reconstruction,"},{"time":433000,"text":"you can train masons"},{"time":435000,"text":"for dollars on every house"},{"time":437000,"text":"that they end up building over their lifetime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442000,"text":"Ultimately, there are two ways"},{"time":444000,"text":"that you can rebuild Haiti;"},{"time":446000,"text":"the way at the top"},{"time":448000,"text":"is the way that Haiti's been building for decades."},{"time":451000,"text":"The way at the top"},{"time":453000,"text":"is a poorly constructed building"},{"time":455000,"text":"that will fail."},{"time":457000,"text":"The way at the bottom is a confined masonry building,"},{"time":460000,"text":"where the walls are tied together,"},{"time":462000,"text":"the building is symmetric,"},{"time":464000,"text":"and it will stand up to an earthquake."},{"time":467000,"text":"For all the disaster,"},{"time":469000,"text":"there is an opportunity here"},{"time":472000,"text":"to build better houses"},{"time":474000,"text":"for the next generation,"},{"time":476000,"text":"so that when the next earthquake hits,"},{"time":479000,"text":"it is a disaster --"},{"time":481000,"text":"but not a tragedy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}